data.name: Slow-Cooked Pork Shoulder with Savory Gravy and Creamy Garlic Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender, slow-cooked pork shoulder served with rich savory gravy and creamy garlic mashed potatoes for a comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Season the pork shoulder generously with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, heat a tablespoon of oil over medium heat and sear the pork on all sides until browned (about 3-4 minutes per side).
Transfer the pork to a slow cooker. Add the diced onion, minced garlic, chicken broth, soy sauce, brown sugar, thyme, and rosemary to the slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or until the pork is tender and easily shredded with a fork.
About 30 minutes before serving, boil the quartered potatoes in salted water until fork-tender (around 15-20 minutes).
Drain the potatoes and return them to the pot. Add butter, heavy cream, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mash until creamy and smooth.
Once the pork is finished cooking, remove it from the slow cooker and shred the meat, reserving the juices.
For the gravy, strain the cooking liquid into a saucepan and simmer until reduced and thickened to your liking.
Serve the shredded pork topped with gravy alongside a generous scoop of creamy garlic mashed potatoes and garnish with chives.
